# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Repolis — OPTIONAL taxi-driver backends (Vercel alternative)
#
# The static site works with NO backend at all: "Local search" is the default
# and "WebLLM" runs on-device, both keyless. Configure a backend ONLY if you
# want the extra AI modes — the taxi silently falls back to Local when these
# are unset, unreachable or slow, so a fresh clone deploys with zero setup.
#
# ⚑ WHICH BACKEND? The LIVE Repolis site runs on the Cloudflare Worker in
#   cloudflare-taxi/ — NOT on these Vercel functions. The Worker is recommended
#   (no ~10s Hobby wall) and is a superset: it also answers off-KB questions
#   in-persona (general chat) via a keyless Entra service principal, and serves
#   multiple scholar NPCs. Its secrets are set with `wrangler secret put` (and a
#   git-ignored .dev.vars for local dev), NOT in this .env — see
#   cloudflare-taxi/README.md. THIS file is only for the optional Vercel path below.
#
# Usage (Vercel path):
#   • Local dev   → copy this file to ".env" and run `vercel dev`
#   • Production  → paste these into Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables
# Never commit real keys. This .env.example holds placeholders only.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ── (A) 🛰️ AI Foundry Live (grounded)  →  api/taxi-grounded.js ───────────────
# Live, grounded answers about your repos via an Azure AI Search Knowledge Base
# whose MCP Knowledge Source calls GitHub's hosted MCP server. This function
# only ever holds a *Search* key — the Azure OpenAI key and the GitHub PAT stay
# server-side inside the Knowledge Source on Azure (never in the browser).

SEARCH_ENDPOINT=https://<your-search>.search.windows.net
SEARCH_API_KEY=<azure-ai-search-admin-or-query-key>
SEARCH_KB_NAME=repolis-github-kb
# Comma-separated knowledge-source name(s) — attach more MCPs here later,
# e.g. github-repos-mcp-ks,microsoft-learn-mcp-ks
SEARCH_KS_NAME=github-repos-mcp-ks

# Optional tuning:
SEARCH_API_VERSION=2026-05-01-preview
GROUNDED_TIMEOUT_MS=9000        # fetch abort (ms); 9000 fits Vercel Hobby's ~10s wall
GROUNDED_MAX_RUNTIME_S=30       # KB runtime budget (seconds); KB requires 11–599
# ALLOW_ORIGIN=https://<you>.github.io   # lock CORS to your Pages origin (default *)
#
# ☁️ Cloudflare Workers (recommended — no ~10s wall): deploy cloudflare-taxi/ instead
#    of (A). Same SEARCH_* values, but set them as Worker secrets/vars rather than in
#    this .env — `wrangler secret put SEARCH_API_KEY` etc. For in-persona general chat
#    the Worker also takes a keyless Entra service principal (AOAI_ENDPOINT, AAD_TENANT,
#    AAD_CLIENT_ID, AAD_CLIENT_SECRET) — see cloudflare-taxi/README.md for the full list.


# ── (B) 🌐 AI proxy (simple)  →  api/taxi.js ────────────────────────────────
# A single Azure OpenAI call that just picks one repo from the shortlist the
# browser already retrieved. Lighter than (A); no Search/KB needed. Not shown
# in the mode dropdown by default — wire it up only if you prefer it over (A).

AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=https://<your-resource>.openai.azure.com
AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT=<deployment-name>
AZURE_OPENAI_KEY=<azure-openai-key>

# Optional:
AZURE_OPENAI_API_VERSION=2024-08-01-preview
# ALLOW_ORIGIN=https://<you>.github.io
